place.name: WOLTERTON
place.gazetteerText: WOLTERTON, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 8 miles W by N of North Walsham r. station. Post town, Aylsham, under Norwich. Acres, 722. Real property, £1,372. Pop., 48. Houses, 13. W. Hall was built in 1741, for Horace Walpole; and belongs now to the Earl of Orford. The living is a rectory, united with Wickmere, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £564.* Patron, the Earl of Orford. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
